metadata.name: life is a (beautiful) mess #1
metadata.description:
when carefully applied, chaos brings things to life.

'life is a (beautiful) mess' was created as i led a certain amount of chaos take control of an animated textile algorithm i'm developing. 
as soon as it happened i realized that it was a great representation of our lives. 
each line represents one of us and the patterns that appear repeatedly are the situations we live which make us move, feel and be in a certain way. 
the image created is the sum of our paths in this life, as they only make sense when we look at them as one.

---

i hope you find it pleasant to watch this animation, how it develops and grows during aprox 1'30"
there are pieces drawn with the 4 typical school pen colors: black, green, blue and red. also a multicolor and a rare dark mode features.


press [s] to capture an image .png
press [r] to reload the animation
click the mouse to stop the animation
doubleclick the mouse to resume the animation

generative art created by mehno using p5js

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #276
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. âThe Bugged Treeââs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations arenât under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as thereâs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: Sashiko #122
metadata.description:
This artwork is inspired by Sashiko - meaning 'little stabs' - which is the traditional Japanese method of repairing fabric with elaborate embroidery designs. This method makes the original fabric thicker, more durable and more beautiful. 
Here the plain coloured textiles take a back seat to the stitching, with simple palettes and layouts.
Keys 2, 3 and 4 will render the artwork at increasing resolutions.

- 2: download 2000px png
- 4: download 4000px png
- 8: download 8000px png
- s: save the image as PNG

When downloading higher resolution pngs, it might take several seconds to redraw the whole image. Download will start immediately after redrawing is completed. Please bear with the slow rendering.

metadata.name: To my lips, your kisses and cigarettes #45
metadata.description:
A timid smoke rises from the ashtray, just a trace of what had been hours before, powerful smoke drifting through the room. A memory of the lighted flames illuminating the faces that were there, coming from many mouths, amid laughter, sips, drags, and lipsticks. 
Red, purple, orange, pink, beige... an ashtray of many palettes, an ashtray of many mouths. 
The smoke goes out and, like the fog that dissipates in the early hours of the day clearing the horizon, I realize: Sophie, Chloe, Lena, Zoe and Kylie... which of these mouths also took my heart?

15 layers
47 images
More than a trillion possibilities 

Laura Faria | @laufaria
2022
Digital Collage

metadata.name: what's left of what's left #17
metadata.description:
"The images is not a closed field of knowledge; it is a whirling, centrifugal field. It is not a fiedl of knowledge like any other; it is a movement demanding all the anthropogical aspects of being and time" Didi-Huberman

Continuing in the experimentation of photography and generative art.

What's left of what's left ... Seeks to take the reflection beyond the simple superimposition of images, highlighting the "human" x "machine" interaction.

The areas of light, fog and shadows present us with image clippings in a large tangle of visual reflections.

The algorithm builds unique images from the combination of different layers, according to a bank of photographs extracted from my own collection. In total, there are six layers containing 10 photographs each, in addition to a base layer containing 20 photos of urban fragments.

In addition, the code implements, in a random and semi-autonomous way, some adaptations such as masking, colorization, rotation and blending modes for specific layers.

* Features
Place - Where have i been. 20 distinct urban fragments;
Mode - âColorâ 80% or âB&Wâ 20%;
Zone - âAmazonâ 25%; âMistâ and âTerracottaâ 20%, âOld Skyâ 15%; and âOcherâ and âGoldenâ 10%.
Invert - 2.5%

"In a sense of overlapping past/future, not as an idea of ââcurrent time, but as places of memory dispute. This "non-place", traversed by layers, is solidified in the images, almost like a truce from the endless war of this inconstancy.
there is no winner" Raffa Gomes

Generative Token by of Morbeck for fxhash

august 21, 2022
